          <title>French lawmakers vote to oust prime minister in the first successful no-confidence vote since 1962</title>
          <description><![CDATA[PARIS (AP) — France’s far-right and left-wing lawmakers joined together to vote Wednesday a no-confidence motion prompted by budget disputes that forces Prime Minister Michel Barnier to resign. The National Assembly approved the motion by 331 votes. A minimum of 288 were needed.]]></description>
